{{Short description|Cameroonian nationalist militant (died 2024)}} {{Infobox person | name = Elisabeth Djouka | image = <!-- filename only, no "File:" or "Image:" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software --> | caption = | birth_name = <!-- only use if different from name --> | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = 11 February 2024 | death_place = | nationality = Cameroonian | other_names = | occupation = Militant | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = }}
'''Elisabeth Djouka''' (died 11 February 2024) was a Cameroonian nationalist militant.<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=12 February 2024|title=Cameroun :: La Combattante Maman Djouka Elisabeth Alias La Douce Est Morte :: Cameroon|trans-title= |url=https://www.camer.be/84383/11:1/cameroun-la-combattante-maman-djouka-elisabeth-alias-la-douce-est-morte-cameroon.html|language=French|work=Camber.be|location= |access-date=20 February 2024}}</ref> She was known for her incarceration in [[Bafoussam]] Prison and her mugshot captioned "outlaw".<ref name="Outlaw">{{cite news |last= |first= |date=8 March 2024|title=Martin Singap et Djouka Elisabeth|trans-title= |url=https://lvslcam.wordpress.com/2018/03/08/page/2/|language=French|work=La vérité sur le Cameroun|location= |access-date=20 February 2024}}</ref>
==Biography== Djouka was originally from [[Bamendjou]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Ketch|first=Arol|date=6 December 2021|title=Soutenons maman Djouka Elisabeth, une combattante oubliée|trans-title= |url=https://www.arolketchraconte.com/2021/12/06/soutenons-maman-djouka-elisabeth-une-combattante-oubliee/|language=French|work=Arol Ketch Raconte|location= |access-date=20 February 2024}}</ref> and took on arms training in [[Batié, Cameroon|Batié]] while she was only a teenager.<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=12 February 2024|title=Le Cameroun pleure la perte d'Elisabeth Djouka, nationaliste engagée|trans-title= |url=https://www.scoopernews.com/2024/02/12/le-cameroun-pleure-la-perte-d-elisabeth-djouka-nationaliste-engag-e/53338568|language=French|work=Scooper|location= |access-date=20 February 2024}}</ref> She was nicknamed "la douce", or "the sweet one" because she cooked food for her fellow militants.
A committed nationalist, Djouka was a young bride and her family believed she had died following her first arrest. She was thrown into Bafoussam Prison<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=2 January 2020|title=Rappel mémoire: 1er janvier 1960, proclamation de l'indépendance du Cameroun|trans-title= |url=http://audanet.afrikblog.com/archives/2020/01/02/37907713.html|language=French|work=Afrikblog|location= |access-date=20 February 2024}}</ref> and became famous from her mugshot, taken in February 1969.<ref name="Outlaw"/> Several sources alleged that she suffered extensive sexual assault, rendering her infertile.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/watch/?v=919866385320538|title=Maman Djouka Elisabeth vous remercie !!|date=22 December 2021|work=Facebook|language=French}}</ref>
Elisabeth Djouka died on 11 February 2024. Her funeral was organised for 2 March 2024.<ref>{{cite news |last=Jackson|first=Joseph|date=20 February 2024|title=Maman Djouka Elisabeth Obituary A Tribute to a Brave Woman in Cameroon|trans-title= |url=https://erldc.org/obituary/maman-djouka-elisabeth-obituary/|language= |work=Entertainment Regional Lifestyle Digital Corner|location= |access-date=20 February 2024}}</ref>

<noinclude>__TOC__</noinclude> {{SPIarchive notice|Siddharthmenon2121}} {{SPIpriorcases}} ===20 February 2024=== {{SPI case status|}} ====Suspected sockpuppets==== {{sock list|1=202.191.65.246|2=Vidhyasuja|tools_link=yes}}<!-- Add more accounts or IPs to this template as needed -->
The first two accounts were both active at [[Siddharth Menon (singer)]] on November 20, adding similar information within 20 minutes or so.[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Siddharth_Menon_(singer)&diff=next&oldid=1186008649][https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Siddharth_Menon_%28singer%29&diff=1186010298&oldid=1186008649] On February 19, the IP address made a large amount of changes to the subject's film credits and awards.[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Siddharth_Menon_%28singer%29&diff=1208913818&oldid=1186075992] Moments later, the sockmaster account began making edits to the infobox photo, claiming to be the subject.[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Siddharth_Menon_%28singer%29&diff=1208916229&oldid=1208915554] After I fixed some header info that had been damaged in a previous edit, and having to restore a previous version to do so, the sockmaster account again stated in an edit summary that they themselves were the subject.[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Siddharth_Menon_%28singer%29&diff=1208925705&oldid=1208919882] Despite a [[WP:COI]] warning from [[User:Czello]],[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Siddharth_Menon_%28singer%29&diff=1208926244&oldid=1208925705] the user continued to edit the article.[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Siddharth_Menon_%28singer%29&diff=1208926367&oldid=1208926244] Minutes later, the IP address began editing again, now claiming to be part of the subject's team.[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Siddharth_Menon_%28singer%29&diff=1208927914&oldid=1208926545] Both accounts received COI warnings from myself and other editors. I opened a case at [[Wikipedia:Conflict of interest/Noticeboard]][https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia%3AConflict_of_interest%2FNoticeboard&diff=1208930572&oldid=1208858806] where [[User:Scope creep]] agreed there was a conflict of interest with both accounts.[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia%3AConflict_of_interest%2FNoticeboard&diff=1208947828&oldid=1208939022] They were then warned again[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=User_talk%3ASiddharthmenon2121&diff=1208947520&oldid=1208933090][https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=User_talk%3A202.191.65.246&diff=1208941946&oldid=1208932217] and the editing seemed to stop. In the meantime, edits were made to the article, removing all of the unsourced information.[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Siddharth_Menon_%28singer%29&diff=1208933057&oldid=1208932317][https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Siddharth_Menon_%28singer%29&diff=1208940035&oldid=1208933057][https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Siddharth_Menon_%28singer%29&diff=1208968206&oldid=1208940035] Today, a third account has returned and re-inserted much, if not all, of the previous deleted unsourced information and instructing editors not to remove it.[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Siddharth_Menon_%28singer%29&diff=1209175682&oldid=1208968206] [[User:NJZombie|NJZombie]] ([[User talk:NJZombie|talk]]) 19:49, 20 February 2024 (UTC) UPDATE: Since filing this report, the current account has made the same claim as the IP account, stating on my talk page that they know the subject personally.[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=User_talk%3ANJZombie&diff=1209203661&oldid=1209203228] Sockmaster account is now asking for editors' phone numbers[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=User_talk:Aadirulez8&diff=prev&oldid=1209165598] and while the newest account is asking me for an e-mail address.[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=User_talk:Vidhyasuja&diff=prev&oldid=1209205819]

National Hydrography Dataset high-resolution flowline data. [http://viewer.nationalmap.gov/viewer/ The National Map], accessed February 18, 2024</ref> | width_min = | width_avg = | width_max = | depth_min = | depth_avg = | depth_max = | discharge1_location= | discharge1_min = | discharge1_avg = | discharge1_max = <!---------------------- BASIN FEATURES --> | source1 = [[Blue Mountains (Pacific Northwest)|Blue Mountains]] | source1_location = near [[Peola, Washington|Peola]] | source1_coordinates= {{coord|46|17|49|N|117|29|37|W}}<ref name="GNIS">{{cite gnis|id=1533429|name=Alpowa Creek|entrydate=September 10, 1979|accessdate=February 19, 2024}}</ref> | source1_elevation = | mouth = [[Snake River]] | mouth_location = West of [[Lewiston, Idaho|Lewiston]]/[[Clarkston, Washington|Clarkston]] | mouth_coordinates = {{coord|46|25|16|N|117|12|15|W|display=inline,title}}<ref name="GNIS"/> | mouth_elevation = {{convert|738|ft|m|abbr=on}}<ref name="GNIS"/> | progression = | river_system = | basin_size = | basin_landmarks = | basin_population = | tributaries_left = | tributaries_right = | waterbodies = | waterfalls = | bridges = | ports = | custom_label = | custom_data = | extra = }} '''Alpowa Creek''' is a stream in [[Garfield County, Washington|Garfield]] and [[Asotin County, Washington|Asotin Counties]], southeastern [[Washington (state)|Washington]]. It starts near [[Peola, Washington|Peola]], about {{convert|10|mi|km}} south of [[Pomeroy, Washington|Pomeroy]], in the foothills of the northern [[Blue Mountains (Pacific Northwest)|Blue Mountains]] just outside the [[Umatilla National Forest]].<ref name="USGS Peola">{{Cite web |url=https://topoquest.com/map-detail.php?usgs_cell_id=34750|title=U.S. Geological Survey Topographic Map: Peola, Washington quad |author=U.S. Geological Survey |publisher=TopoQuest |access-date=February 18, 2024}}</ref> It initially flows north through farmland before descending northeast into a canyon, flanked to the north by Alpowa Ridge and to the south by Knotgrass Ridge.<ref name="USGS Alpowa Ridge">{{Cite web |url=https://topoquest.com/map-detail.php?usgs_cell_id=710|title=U.S. Geological Survey Topographic Map: Alpowa Ridge, Washington quad |author=U.S. Geological Survey |publisher=TopoQuest |access-date=February 18, 2024}}</ref> It receives Stember Creek from the left; downstream of there, [[U.S. Highway 12]] runs parallel to it.<ref name="USGS Stember Creek">{{Cite web |url=https://topoquest.com/map-detail.php?usgs_cell_id=43086|title=U.S. Geological Survey Topographic Map: Stember Creek, Washington quad |author=U.S. Geological Survey |publisher=TopoQuest |access-date=February 18, 2024}}</ref> It empties into the Snake River at [[Lower Granite Lake]], the impoundment formed by [[Lower Granite Dam]], about {{convert|8|mi|km}} to the west of [[Clarkston, Washington|Clarkston]].<ref name="USGS Silcott Island">{{Cite web |url=https://topoquest.com/map-detail.php?usgs_cell_id=41326|title=U.S. Geological Survey Topographic Map: Silcott Island, Washington quad |author=U.S. Geological Survey |publisher=TopoQuest |access-date=February 18, 2024}}</ref>
The creek's name derives from the [[Nez Perce language|Nez Perce]] ''Alpahwah'' or ''Elpawawe'' meaning "a spring forming a creek", which was the name of a Nez Perce village that once stood at the confluence of Alpowa Creek and the Snake River.<ref>{{cite book|title=Origin of Washington Geographic Names|author=Meany, Edmond Stephen|publisher=University of Washington Press|isbn=9780598974808}}</ref>{{rp|6}} The creek supports a minor population of Snake River [[steelhead trout]]. Due to the impacts of livestock grazing and water diversion for agriculture, it has been designated a priority restoration reach by the Snake River Salmon Recovery Board.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://srp.rco.wa.gov/project/320/14896|title=MSA Alpowa Creek|publisher=Salmon Recovery Portal|date=|accessdate=February 20, 2024}}</ref>
